tcela-7 is an MP@ML bitstream created for the Video Conformance Testing AHG,
for the "Frequent slices" test (long version = 61 frames).

Parameters are the following:

Bitstream ID:   5 (long version).
Description:    Frequent slices (e.g. 1 Slice = 1 MB)
Stresses:       VLD and parser
Justification:  CPU-oriented designs have large overhead for each Slice header.
Parameters:     MP@ML, 61 frames
Organization:   TCE-LA

Bit rate:               15 Mbit/sec 
Sampling dimensions:    720  x 480 x 30 Hz 
vbv_buffer_size:        1.75 Mbit/sec (maximum vbv_buffer_size) 
Distribution of bits:   observed rule of maximum 2 macroblocks per row
                        that exceed legal 1.5:1 expansion factor.

Note that, although the parameters are similar to tcela-6, tcela-6 is not
the beginning of tcela-7.

Please check that you can decode it.  Thank-you.

        Bitstream file             tcela-7.bits
        Reconstructed frames*      tcela-7.decoded
        Decoding trace **          tcela-7.trace
        picture structure          I P B B P B B ... (frame-structure)

        *frame format:

                4:2:0 frame ("display" order) 8 bit

                       width
                +---------------+
                |               |
                |      Y0       | height
                |width/2        |
                +-------+-------+
                |  Cb0  | height/2
                +-------+
                |  Cr0  | height/2
                +-------+-------+
                |               |
                |      Y1       |
                |               |
                +-------+-------+
                |       |
                  etc...

        ** Only the first row of MBs is traced.
           More complete traces are available on special order.


Best regards,

Tristan

